---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';

import { interactiveFiction } from '@constants/blog';

const meta = {
  title: 'Blog | CoNexus',
  nav: 'Blog',
  arrow: '/learn/blog',
  header: 'Create Interactive Fiction',
  subheading:
    'Want to create interactive fiction? Discover the best tools, platforms, and techniques to start building branching narratives and story games online in 2025 — no coding required.',
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>
  <header class="blog-title">
    <img
      class="shad-behind"
      src="/learn/blog/create-interactive-fiction.avif"
      alt="Interactive fiction"
    />
    <h3>Create Interactive Fiction: Tools and Tips for Storytellers in 2025</h3>
  </header>

  <article class="blog-page">
    <p>
      Interactive fiction combines the art of storytelling with the engagement
      of choice-driven gameplay. It allows readers to participate in the
      narrative by making decisions that impact the plot, characters, and world
      around them. Whether you’re an aspiring writer, game designer, or someone
      with a story to tell, creating interactive fiction is more accessible than
      ever in 2025.
    </p>
    <p>
      This guide outlines the best tools and practical advice to help you build
      immersive, branching stories — even if you’ve never coded before.
    </p>
    <hr />
    <h5>Why Create Interactive Fiction?</h5>
    <p>Interactive fiction gives you the chance to:</p>
    <ul class="default-ul">
      <li>Let readers shape the outcome of your story</li>
      <li>Build nonlinear narratives with replayable paths</li>
      <li>Deepen engagement through branching perspectives</li>
      <li>
        Explore alternate realities, moral dilemmas, and layered character arcs
      </li>
      <li>
        Connect with readers through active participation rather than passive
        consumption
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      It’s a powerful format for anyone looking to explore new dimensions of
      storytelling.
    </p>
    <hr />
    <h5>Best Platforms to Create Interactive Fiction in 2025:</h5>
    <ol class="cards-list">
      {
        interactiveFiction.map(
          ({ name, bestFor, platform, pricing, description, url }) => {
            return (
              <a
                class={name === 'CoNexus' ? 'card green-card' : 'card'}
                href={url}
              >
                <h4>{name}</h4>
                <span class="details">
                  <p>
                    Best for: <strong>{bestFor}</strong>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    Platform: <strong>{platform}</strong>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    Pricing: <strong>{pricing}</strong>
                  </p>
                </span>
                <p>{description}</p>
              </a>
            );
          }
        )
      }
    </ol>
    <hr />
    <h5>Tips for Creating Strong Interactive Fiction</h5>
    <ol class="default-ol">
      <li>
        If you want full creative control and scripting power, try Ink or
        ChoiceScript.
      </li>
      <li>If you're focused on visual novels, go for RenPy.</li>
      <li>
        If you want a modern, no-code experience with built-in replayability,
        AI-generated visuals, and flexible customization, explore CoNexus.
      </li>
    </ol>
    <hr />
    <h5>Final Thoughts</h5>
    <p>
      Creating interactive fiction doesn’t require a studio budget or technical
      expertise anymore. With modern tools like CoNexus, Twine, and Ink, anyone
      can build complex, emotionally resonant stories that give readers agency
      and engagement.
    </p>
    <p>Start writing today — and let your audience shape what happens next.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>
